    {
      "instruction": "<p>Return the reserved pan to a medium-high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>sliced onion</strong>, <strong>pepper strips </strong>and <strong>bay leaf[ves]<span class=\"text-danger\"> </span></strong>with a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and <strong>pepper </strong>and cook for 4-5 min or until beginning to soften</p><p>Dissolve your <strong>chicken stock mix </strong>in 250ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[325ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[450ml]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong></p>",
