    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once softened, add the <strong>chopped garlic</strong>, <strong>ground</strong> <strong>smoked paprika</strong>, <strong>tomato wedges</strong> and <strong>tomato paste</strong> and cook for 1-2 min or until fragrant</p><p>Once fragrant, add the <strong>chicken stock </strong>to the pan with 1 tsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tsp]</span> <strong>sugar</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to medium and cook for 5-6 min or until the vegetables are tender and the stock has thickened to a stew-like consistency</p>",
